      • getZoo

        public void getZoo​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
        This method is called when the user selects a zoo from the choice box. It gets the name of the selected zoo, sets it to the label 'myLabel', and sets the corresponding image to 'IM'. It also checks if a time has been selected, and sets the 'STATUS' label to "CLOSED" if no time is selected or the selected time is outside the zoo's opening hours.
        Parameters:
        event - the event of selecting a zoo from the choice box
